==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*finþanan''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[finda]], Old Saxon ''findan'' (Dutch [[vinden]]), Old High German ''findan'' (German [[finden]]), Old Norse [[finna]] (Swedish [[finna]]), Gothic [[𐍆𐌹𐌽𐌸𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'fɪndan/}}

===Verb===
'''findan''' (class III strong: ''3 singular present'' '''[[findeþ]]''', ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[fand]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[fundon]]''', ''past participle'' (ġe)'''[[funden]]''')
# to [[find]], [[meet]]

